בּרך / bârak / baw-rak'
=== Etymology ===

A primitive root; 
=== Verb ===
to [[kneel]]; by implication to [[bless]] God (as an act of adoration), and (vice-versa) man (as a benefit); also (by euphemism) to curse (God or the king, as treason): -  X abundantly, X altogether, X at all, blaspheme, [[bless]], congratulate, curse, X greatly, X indeed, kneel (down), [[praise]], salute, X still, thank.